records.addlTxt:
Defendant Reginald L Harris in court with attorney Richard A. Sachs.  Defendant Reginald L Harris in custody.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. Letters on behalf of the defendant received and filed. PSI reviewed by the parties. State placed negotiations on the record. Statements made as to sentencing. 

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 7 YEARS, with credit for 159 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4 YEARS.  

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 4 YEARS with the following conditions:

1) Court ordered 9 MONTHS of condition time in the House of Correction. Defendant may have release to the Day Reporting Center, and may participate in educational and vocational programming at the House of Correction;
2) Restitution set at ZERO;
3) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
4) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
5) No contact with the co-defendant Norman Boose;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety from all illegal drugs and alcohol;
7) Participate in a cognitive thinking program;
8) Attend parenting class;
9) Maintain verifiable employment of at least 30 hours per week. If not employed 30 hours per week, be enrolled in an educational program;
10) AODA assessment and comply with recommended treatment;
11) Obtain HSED;
12) Participate in vocational programming;

Court ordered the cash bail in the amount of $250.00 be reinstated and applied towards the costs, fees and surcharges. 

If revoked, defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

If revoked, court costs, fees, and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds/earnings.

It is the court's intention the conditions of probation be the same as the conditions of extended supervision if the defendant is revoked.


Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
